      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved gradation must meet or exceed required gradation for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI—volume-averaged shear stress and the derived relative hemolysis index—directly maps to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model is the regulatory standard for CFD hemolysis in blood-contacting devices. Achieved gradation 2 meets the required gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
